        "title": "Smile detection on server side",
        "body": "<p>I have to do application that detects your smile. I've decided to do client side with AngularJS, having REST services on server side that are processing image and maybe returning information if smile was detected.<\/p>\n\n<p>I've found <a href=\"https://github.com/jonashartmann/webcam-directive\" rel=\"nofollow\">webcam library<\/a> that allows me to take snapshot of user webcam. It works fine by now, but when I'm sending by POST this image to my (local) server, it goes very laggy after a time and one frame has 3-4 s delay. I'm sending frame to server every 600 ms.<\/p>\n\n<p>I'm asking for ideas to optimize this workflow - maybe my assumptions were bad and application should have another architecture?<\/p>\n",
